<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ROI Calculator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>ROI Calculator for Marketing Campaigns</h1>
        <form id="roiForm" class="form-style">
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="adSpend">Ad Spend ($):</label>
                <input type="number" id="adSpend" name="adSpend" required>
            </div>
            
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="conversionRate">Conversion Rate (%):</label>
                <input type="number" id="conversionRate" name="conversionRate" required>
            </div>
            
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="averageDeal">Average Deal Size ($):</label>
                <input type="number" id="averageDeal" name="averageDeal" required>
            </div>
            
            <button type="button" class="btn-primary" onclick="calculateROI()">Calculate ROI</button>
        </form>
        
        <div id="result">
            <h2>Understanding Your ROI Calculation:</h2>
            <p>The Return on Investment (ROI) is calculated using the following formula:</p>
            <p><strong>ROI = ((Revenue - Ad Spend) / Ad Spend) * 100%</strong></p>
            <p>The revenue is determined by multiplying your conversion rate by the ad spend and the average deal size. This provides an estimate of how much revenue your marketing campaign generates relative to the cost of running the campaign.</p>
            <h2>Your ROI: <span id="roiValue"></span></h2>
            <button id="savePdf" class="btn-secondary">Save Results as PDF</button>
            <button id="contactButton" class="btn-primary">Contact Us</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="/js/scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
